node.text: Photo by @amivitale | The sun rises over the beach at Weligama, a town on the south coast of Sri Lanka. The name Weligama, literally means "sandy village" which refers to the area's sandy sweep bay. Today, Sri Lanka is known for its beautiful white beaches, wildlife and culture. The country’s civil war ended in 2009  and the hope is that it can move forward and begin to solve some of the issues of postwar reconciliation, a story I covered for National Geographic (@natgeo). Follow @amivitale for more uplifting stories from around the world. @natgeoimagecollection @natgeo @thephotosociety #beach #srilanka #asia #palmtrees

From 1 to 6, which country would you like to visit...😍?

node.text: Photo by @CristinaMittermeier | I wanted to make a portrait of this young boy but he was too shy, so instead of posing, he dropped backwards, laughing into the long grass in the El Triunfo Biosphere Reserve, in Chiapas, Mexico. I loved capturing this moment because he looked so content and at peace with the world. This boy lives in a Tzotzil Maya community, which makes up about one-third of the state’s indigenous population. They often do grueling work in coffee plantations and are the people who make our shade-grown, sustainable cups of coffee possible. #FollowMe at @CristinaMittermeier for more photos that celebrate #Gratitude from around the world. #Mexico #community #smile #Enoughness
